House Resolution 236
By: Representatives Gambill of the 15th and Scoggins of the 14th
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Linda Ford Kellogg on her outstanding service; and for other
2 purposes.
3 WHEREAS, Linda Ford Kellogg has diligently and conscientiously devoted innumerable
4 hours of her time, talents, and energy toward the betterment of her community and state, as
5 evidenced dramatically by her 35 years of superlative service as chairperson of the MLK
6 Holiday Weekend festivities in Bartow County, Georgia; and
7 WHEREAS, her professional career spans a wide range of important roles, including
8 positions at Cass High School, Cass #2 Elementary School, the District Attorney's Office,
9 the Governor's Office, the Adult Probation Office, and Hickory Log Vocational School, as
10 well as nearly sixteen years in banking; and
11 WHEREAS, throughout her distinguished tenure in education, she dedicated 22 years of
12 service to Cartersville City Schools, during which time she served as attendance director,
13 secretary, and administrative assistant at Cartersville High School; and
14 WHEREAS, following her retirement, she was asked to return to Cartersville High School
15 as a consultant handling student services, where she continued to support students and faculty
