16 for an additional ten years while serving on multiple school committees, including the School
17 Council and Leadership Team; and
18 WHEREAS, Linda Ford Kellogg has additionally served as an issuing officer for youth
19 employment certificates with the Georgia Department of Labor since 2006 and was the first
20 African American mediator in Bartow County; and
21 WHEREAS, she has further played a pivotal role in local elections since 1971 and made
22 history as the first African American to serve as elections manager for the Zena Drive
23 Precinct in Bartow County; and
24 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding accomplishments of this
25 remarkable and distinguished Georgian be appropriately honored.
26 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
27 the members of this body recognize and commend Linda Ford Kellogg for her efficient,
28 effective, unselfish, and dedicated service to her community; congratulate her upon the grand
29 occasion of her retirement; and extend the most sincere best wishes for continued health and
30 happiness.
31 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
32 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Linda
33 Ford Kellogg.
